Returns: The newly initiated @B_com#google#android#gms#games#multiplayer#turnbased#TurnBasedMatch_E@ object. Note that this may be null, depending on the status code returned.

ClassDesc: Result delivered when match has been initiated. This happens when the player creates a new match, or when the player joins an existing match. Possible status codes include: @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_OK_E@ if data was successfully loaded and is up-to-date. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_MATCH_ERROR_ALREADY_REMATCHED_E@ if this is an attempt to rematch a match which has already had a rematch created. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_OPERATION_FAILED_E@ if the attempt to initiate the match failed due to network error. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_MULTIPLAYER_ERROR_NOT_TRUSTED_TESTER_E@ if one of the users in the match is not a trusted tester of a game which is not yet published. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_MULTIPLAYER_ERROR_INVALID_OPERATION_E@ if the server rejected the operation. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_MULTIPLAYER_DISABLED_E@ if the game does not support multiplayer. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_CLIENT_RECONNECT_REQUIRED_E@ if the client needs to reconnect to the service to access this data. @B_com#google#android#gms#games#GamesStatusCodes#STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR_E@ if an unexpected error occurred in the service.
